      "content": "You should set your story in a place where the decay is visible in the very fabric of the neighborhood, perhaps featuring abandoned factories or crumbling tenements. The atmosphere should be thick with the smell of stale refuse and something metallic, like old blood or rust. Focus on the constant, low-level soundscape—distant sirens, rattling ventilation shafts, and the muffled shouts from unseen windows—to build that pervasive dread. These areas feel inherently dangerous because they are neglected by the world, and that neglect breeds something sinister.",
