      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing on the existing societal tensions and the way the neighborhood is perceived by outsiders can amplify the tension. You can use the constant presence of police surveillance juxtaposed with areas where authority has completely broken down to create a sense of no-man's-land. The unspoken rules and the deep-seated community mistrust can make the environment itself feel hostile, where every shadow might hide someone who operates outside the law. This sense of pervasive, internalized danger makes the setting feel authentically suffocating.",
      "source": "target",
